arch:property.oc:show_val: This soil is Munsell Brown 7.5YR 5/3 and it is homogeneous in character being filled with tiles, bricks, mortar, stones, ash, and charcoal indicating that it is a destruction locus. It is a consistent thick dusty deposit with collapsed ashlars and opus sectile elements, crushed brick, gravel aggregate, and mortar. The ceramic corpus is primarily composed of broken flue pipes or tubuli.
Phase XII: Use levels, robbing and abandonments continue.

Phase XI: Further collapse post- CE 5th c., possibly the result of the earthquake of CE 512. Major collapses in the Lower Temenos lead to the continued accumulation of fill. At this time the East Colonnade collapses significantly onto a bed of accumulated soil, as does the entablature of the East Exedra.
